sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client Application<br/>(e.g., TrustyAI)
    participant Server as NeMo Guardrails Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant InputRails as Input Rails<br/>(injection, jailbreak,<br/>topic, PII detection)
    participant Engine as LLMRails Engine<br/>(Colang Runtime)
    participant EmbIdx as Embedding Index<br/>(FastEmbed + Annoy)
    participant LLM as Backend LLM Endpoint<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant OutputRails as Output Rails<br/>(hallucination, factcheck,<br/>content safety)
    participant OTel as OpenTelemetry Collector<br/>4317/TCP gRPC

    Note over Client,OTel: Flow 1: Chat Completion with Guardrails

    Client->>Server: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTP (plaintext), No Auth
    Server->>InputRails: Apply input rails
    InputRails->>Engine: Evaluate Colang flows
    Engine->>EmbIdx: Retrieve relevant context<br/>(RAG knowledge base)
    EmbIdx-->>Engine: Matching documents

    alt Input rails PASS
        Engine->>LLM: Forward to LLM<br/>HTTPS/443, API Key Auth
        LLM-->>Engine: LLM Response
        Engine->>OutputRails: Apply output rails
        OutputRails->>Engine: Evaluate output safety

        alt Output rails PASS
            Engine-->>Server: Approved response
            Server-->>Client: JSON Response<br/>HTTP 200
        else Output rails FAIL
            Engine-->>Server: Blocked/modified response
            Server-->>Client: Guardrail intervention<br/>HTTP 200 (modified content)
        end
    else Input rails FAIL
        Engine-->>Server: Request blocked
        Server-->>Client: Guardrail rejection<br/>HTTP 200 (refusal message)
    end

    Server->>OTel: Export tracing spans<br/>gRPC/4317, TLS

    Note over Client,OTel: Flow 2: Streaming Chat Completion (SSE)

    Client->>Server: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>stream=true, HTTP
    Server->>Engine: Process with guardrails
    Engine->>LLM: Forward to LLM<br/>HTTPS/443, API Key Auth
    LLM-->>Engine: Streaming tokens
    Engine-->>Server: Apply streaming output rails
    Server-->>Client: HTTP SSE stream<br/>(Server-Sent Events)
